<item>
            <title>[JDK-8310054] ScrollPane insets are incorrect</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8310054</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>After the size of ScrollPane child component changes, it recalculates the size of the scroll bars and hides or shows them as necessary. This situation is handled in WScrollPanePeer.childResized.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
After &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8297923&quot; title=&quot;java.awt.ScrollPane broken after multiple scroll up/down&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8297923&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8297923&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, setSpans is run asynchronously on the toolkit thread, so setInsets which follows it sets the incorrect values.</description>
